headlines.description: — The Miami Heat were coming off back-to-back losses and missing four regulars including their leading scorer, so Kyle Lowry sensed a need to score more.
headlines.shortLinkText: Lowry leads 3-point barrage in Heat win over Pacers

headlines.description: — Darius Garland had 32 points, 10 assists and eight rebounds, and the Cleveland Cavaliers went on a 19-0 run spanning part of each half in a 116-101 rout of the Washington Wizards on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Cavs extend winning streak to 4 with 116-101 rout of Wizards

headlines.description: — After playing only .500 ball through 22 games, the Philadelphia 76ers finally produced a win capable of turning around their season.
headlines.shortLinkText: Embiid's late jumper caps 76ers' rally past Hawks, 98-96

headlines.description: — Kevin Durant scored 30 points, including the clinching jumper with 11 seconds left, and the Brooklyn Nets held off the Minnesota Timberwolves 110-105 on Friday night.
— Eric Gordon scored 24 points and his short jumper with 1.6 seconds left lifted the Houston Rockets to their fifth consecutive win, 118-116 over the Orlando Magic on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gordon's late shot lifts Rockets over Magic 118-116

events.name: New Orleans Pelicans at Dallas Mavericks

headlines.description: — Brandon Ingram scored 24 points and New Orleans beat Dallas 107-91 on Friday night, two days after the Pelicans lost by 32 to the Mavericks at home while letting them set a franchise record for shooting percentage.
headlines.shortLinkText: Pelicans overtake Mavs 107-91, answer blowout loss to Dallas

headlines.description: — Donovan Mitchell had 34 points and six assists to lead the Utah Jazz over the Boston Celtics 137-130 Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Mitchell scores 34, leads Jazz past Celtics 137-130

events.name: Phoenix Suns at Golden State Warriors

headlines.description: — Warriors coach Steve Kerr spent a good chunk of his postgame press conference reiterating his belief that the Suns are the best team in the West.
headlines.shortLinkText: Curry bounces back, Warriors end Suns' 18-game streak 118-96

events.name: LA Clippers at Los Angeles Lakers

headlines.description: — LeBron James returned from a frustrating stint in the NBA's health and safety protocols just in time for yet another frustrating loss for the Los Angeles Lakers.
headlines.shortLinkText: Kennard hits clutch 3s, Clippers hold off Lakers 119-115
